# Git workflow

Always sync with `origin/main` before starting new work, pushing, or opening/updating a PR.

## Required sequence

```bash
git fetch origin
git checkout main
git pull --ff-only origin main
```

If `--ff-only` fails, reconcile locally (merge or rebase) before continuing.

## When to run it

- **Before creating a new branch**:

```bash
git fetch origin
git checkout main
git pull --ff-only origin main
git checkout -b <new-branch>
```

- **Before pushing commits (feature branch)**:

```bash
git fetch origin
git pull origin main
```

Use merge or rebase per team preference, but do not push a branch that hasn’t integrated the latest `main`.

- **Before opening/updating a PR**: same as before pushing—integrate latest `main` on the PR branch and resolve conflicts locally.

